title: Star Wars Episode III Reflection
text: Star Wars: Episode III – Revenge of the Sith is the culmination of the prequel trilogy, showing Anakin Skywalker’s tragic fall to the dark side and the rise of the Empire. The film covers critical events like the Clone Wars ending, Order 66, and Anakin becoming Darth Vader. Visually, it features stunning space battles, lightsaber duels, and iconic planets such as Mustafar and Coruscant.

title: Star Wars Episode III Reflection

title: Star Wars Episode III Reflection
text:
Reflection
Watching Episode III again, I was struck by how much the film balances political intrigue with personal tragedy. Anakin’s internal conflict is central, and Hayden Christensen’s portrayal really conveys the tension between his loyalty, fear, and ambition. I also appreciated how the film connects the prequels to the original trilogy, giving context to Darth Vader’s character and the Empire’s rise.

title: Emmett Stralka’s E155-Website
text: Emmett Stralka is a Harvey Mudd College student majoring in Engineering and Economics with a strong background in product management, digital electronics, and UX/UI design. He has completed internships at Ford, Abercrombie & Fitch, and North American Switchgear, gaining experience in both technical engineering and business-focused roles. Actively involved in advanced rocketry, robotics, and signal processing projects, Emmett combines hands-on hardware expertise with analytical problem-solving. He is also a varsity track and field athlete and SCIAC champion, balancing technical rigor with competitive athletics. Passionate about innovation, design, and practical impact, he thrives at the intersection of engineering, economics, and leadership. You can find more projects Emmett has done [here].(https://github.com/stremme1/E155-Website-Emmett_Stralka)
